HTML :
<input type="number" id="tempInput"> → Input field for temperature
<select id="unitSelector"> → Dropdown to choose unit
<button id="convertBtn"> → Convert button
<p id="result"> → Displays the converted temperature

CSS :
padding: 10px; → Styles inputs and buttons
border-radius: 5px; → Rounds edges
color: #333; → Text color for readability

JavaScript :
parseFloat(document.getElementById("tempInput").value) → Converts input to a number
if-else → Checks which unit is selected
innerText → Updates the result text
onclick → Runs the conversion function when the button is clicked
